snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve always envied women with her body type so much! I loved dancing and gymnastics as a kid, but I was so self conscious when I went through puberty (scoring systems in gymnastics were ridiculous when it came to breasts in particular back then, so it was something I had to think about very early on) so I simply stopped doing all of it, for fear I was making a mockery of the sport, because the movements didn’t suit the body type I was growing into (at least not the way I saw them in my head). When I couldn’t do anything without looking awkward as hell the first go or two... I was just so discouraged, I stopped dancing as well.

Heath being so unsure of his ability, but willing to try anyway (and still looking decent doing it) really makes me question if I should just do it anyway. I might not do as well as heath, but dammit does he make it look fun to try regardless. Maybe Ill try to rediscover that part of myself...

Cute video guys. Definitely inspiring ❤️
